Title: An Act to Change the Limits on Candidates' Communications with
Official Title: An Act to Change the Limits on Candidates' Communications with
Number of Sections: 1
Source: versions - Documents and Disposition
Media Type: application/pdf
Strikethrough Detection: 2 sections found

================================================================================

Section 1:
132nd MAINE LEGISLATURE
FIRST REGULAR SESSION-2025
Legislative Document No. 199
S.P. 86 In Senate, January 14, 2025
Voters at the Polls
Reference to the Committee on Veterans and Legal Affairs suggested and ordered printed.
DAREK M. GRANT
Secretary of the Senate
Presented by Senator LIBBY of Cumberland.
Cosponsored by Representative BOYER of Poland and
Representative: POMERLEAU of Standish.
Printed on recycled paper
1 Be it enacted by the People of the State of Maine as follows:
2 Sec. 1. 21-A MRSA §682, sub-§2, as amended by PL 2023, c. 109, §1, is further
3 amended by repealing the first blocked paragraph and enacting the following in its place:
4 These limitations do not prohibit a candidate from attending the voting place and orally
5 communicating with voters the name of the office that the candidate is seeking on the ballot
6 for the election that day and the party or political designation of the candidate as listed on
7 the ballot for the election that day as long as the candidate does not attempt to influence
8 their vote.
9 SUMMARY
1100 This bill amends the law governing prohibition of certain political activities at a voting
1111 place to allow a candidate to orally communicate with voters the name of the office that
1122 the candidate is seeking in the election that day and the candidate's party or political
1133 designation, as it is listed on the ballot for the election that day, as long as the candidate
1144 does not attempt to influence their vote.
Page 1 - 132LR0242(01)
